    "created_at": "2014-11-19T02:26:35Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-11-19T02:26:35Z",
    "body": "Personally, I find it confusing when a plugin overrides my settings. If I `set textwidth=80` in my `.vimrc`, I don't expect that to get changed as soon as I open a rust file. I only expect the plugin to overide my settings if it's required by the file's syntax, such as using tabs in makefiles.\n\nThere doesn't seem to be a convention that vim syntax files follow here, but I'd say it makes sense to go by the princple of least suprise. What do other vim users think?\n",
    "author_association": "NONE",
